King, who declined to talk to me, is said to be confident that his team can=
 fix the movie. He=E2=80=99s booked soundstages for March and informed key =
cast and crew of the need to
reconvene. A source at Lionsgate is similarly hopeful that King can resolve=
 the issues in time to hit that October release date. (Universal has a jam-=
packed 2026 slate, so there aren=E2=80=99t many dates to put Michael if fur=
ther delays are needed.)=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0

=C2=A0

The good news, according to everyone I spoke with, is that the usable foota=
ge they do have is impressive. Jackson=E2=80=99s nephew delivers as Michael=
, and
the musical sequences play big, like something you=E2=80=99d want to watch =
in Imax. Time after time, Jackson=E2=80=99s millions of fans have chosen to=
 celebrate his music and larger-than-life persona=E2=80=94and ignore the al=
legations that consumed the final third of his life. So I=E2=80=99m betting=
 Michael, if it ultimately pleases the fans, will be a global hit in the ve=
in of King=E2=80=99s Bohemian Rhapsody, and nobody in the real world will c=
are about any of these extraordinary behind-the-scenes problems. That
is, of course, if the movie is actually released.=C2=A0

